        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 6:27PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 627 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Salem, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
New Albany, Clarksville, Charlestown, Sellersburg, Galena, Blue
River, New Pekin, Borden, Greenville, and Saint Joseph.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
